lead_paragraph: We yesterday received later Texas papers,. The Telegraph of the 12th inst. thinks that the failure of the Cuban expedition will help on the new republic of Sierra Madre, which, according to that paper, is a fixed fact. It says--"Whatever may be the power of the General Government to prevent the Cuban volunteers from prosecuting their expedition, it cannot prevent its citizens from emigrating to the Northern Provinces of Mexico.
